  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a food processor, grind the peanuts into a fine powder.",
    "In a bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, and vanilla extract.",
    "Add the sugar, flour, and salt to the bowl and mix until a batter forms.",
    "Add the peanut powder and mix until just combined.",
    "Heat a small amount of butter in a skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add the lemon zest and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the ground ginger and cook for 30 seconds, until fragrant.",
    "Pour the batter into a parchment-lined papillote packet and fold the edges to seal.",
    "Bake for 15-20 minutes, until the papillote is puffed and golden brown.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with dried rose petals.",
    "Be careful when opening the papillote, as it will be hot."
  ],
